A_562 - Generally in interpersonal relationships, lies are considered a problem. Sometimes, however, it happens that you don't want to say something to a person, or you don't want to continue a discussion. In that case you can use creative lies, that is, very exaggerated and imaginative lies, which do not deceive the other person's understanding into understanding that you are telling them nonsense. The problem with lies is that they make people become more obtuse, when instead, even in the lie, you manage to be intelligent and creative then in that case there is no problem in using them ... the important thing is that the other person knows perfectly well that it is a lie ... (as in theater or cinematography ...)